INSERT INTO Job VALUES ('S11111110', 'Software Engineering','2023/03/17', 'full-time','The team is responsible for infrastructure systems, including Storage/Computing/DB. We aim to be the leading SRE team across the industry. In the SRE team, you will have the opportunity to manage the complex challenges of scale, while using expertise in coding, algorithms, complexity analysis, and large-scale system design. We embrace a culture of diversity, intellectual curiosity, openness, and problem-solving. We also encourage ownership, self-governance and independence to work on various projects, and an environment that provides the support and mentorship needed to learn and grow as an engineer.',
'1. Reliability: Ensuring the reliability and efficiency of our core infrastructure, focusing on system capacity and stability; setting up reliability standards and recovery SOP.
2. Reliability: Troubleshooting and locating the technical issues, bottleneck analysis, managing system high availability architecture transformation and upgrading.
3. Efficiency: Building automated operation solutions for large-scale systems; partnering with system development teams for system iteration.
4. Efficiency: Designing and implementing software platforms and monitoring frameworks for efficient, automated, and intelligent service-oriented architecture (SOA) governance.
5. Cost: There are millions of CPUs. We should build delivery standards, and monitor and budget systems to optimize the cost of the company.
6. Compliance: Designing and setting up new IDC; designing and implementing data protection plan to meet the standard requirement.',
'What you should have: - Bachelor''s / Master''s Degree in Computer Science or related major, with at least 4 years of relevant experience.
- Solid basic knowledge of computer software, understanding of Linux operating system, storage, network IO and other related principles.
- Familiar with one or more programming languages, such as Python, Go, and Java. Knowledge of design patterns and coding principles is necessary.
Preference will be given to those who have one of the following:
1. Experience with storage, and relevant system experience with the following: KV, Table, Graph, Redis, MySQL, MongoDB, MQ, and Kafka.
2. Experience with computing & big data, and system experience with the following: Kubernetes, Docker/Containers, AIops, Spark, Flink, Function as a service, RPC Framework, and Service Mesh.');

INSERT INTO Job VALUES ('D11111111', 'Data Analytics','2023/03/17', 'full-time','The Product Data Analytics Team analyses a combination of product usage and product performance data to derive meaningful insights that would serve as a guide to better product and decision making for our business leaders. The team will work through different business scenarios including improving Live app Experiences, Host Operation, User experiences. In addition, it is important to manage the data life cycle to ensure problems are quantitatively measured to propose logical solutions.',
'- Responsible for the data analytics work in international LIVE business, including but not limited to live gifts, agency platforms, compliance platform and efficiency platforms.
- Identify and analyse key factors driving the growth of international LIVE, and propose enhancement plans with logical data support.
- Responsible for the design and analysis of A/B experiments, product iteration impact evaluation, marketing campaign analysis, key metrics trend analysis, etc.
- Work with cross functional partners like Product Managers, Operations, R&D for product optimisation plans and boost business growth.
- Perform market activity analysis and any other analytics that would help guide product and business in decision making.',
'1. Bachelor degree or above in Computer Science, Statistics, Mathematics or other related majors.
2. Proficient in SQL, skilled use of visualisation tools.
3. Experience in data extraction, analysis and visualisation in a complex data environment, and have experience in data landing to the business.
4. Excellent communication skills with the ability to communicate conclusions effectively to both technical and non-technical audiences, and good analysis report writing ability.
5. Strong learning ability and curiosity driven mindset, independent and possess collaborative problem solving skills.');

INSERT INTO Job VALUES ('F11111112', 'Finance','2023/03/18', 'full-time','In line with the globalization strategy and vision of the company, the Global Payments team builds a platform to provide cross-border payment solutions for all ByteDance''s products and services, that are growing rapidly worldwide.',
'- Lead of team of investigators and analysts responsible for the investigation and disposition of transaction monitoring alerts.
- Work with the TM Head on alert management, case capacity and Transaction Monitoring tuning.
- Develop and maintain procedures which meet regulatory requirements around transaction monitoring investigations.',
'- Leadership experience and 7 + years of investigtions and transaction monitoring experience.
- Work experience in suspicious transaction analysis and reporting, experience in new risk mining and risk research is preferred.
- Understand the suspicious transaction analysis system and process, and be able to follow up, feedback and improve the process.
- Experience in a previous financial institution and/or Fintech.
- Down-to-earth, self-driven, strong sense of responsibility, willing to settle down to do risk exploration and risk research.
- Logical framework, able to think independently and solve problems and dismantle difficulties, good at communication, strong initiative and execution, especially pay attention to teamwork.
- Result-oriented, strong ability to resist pressure.');



INSERT INTO Job VALUES ('D11111113', 'Designer','2023/03/18', 'full-time','We are looking for passionate and talented engineers to join us to build up and optimize a real-time, high-performance, large-scale distributed infrastructure for live streaming at TikTok. We will be deeply involved in the developmental lifecycle of critical product features, and collaborate closely with product managers to deliver the best live streaming experience for live streamers and viewers. 
TikTok LIVE Revenue engineering team is responsible for building the cutting-edge revenue ecosystem which includes gifting and other revenue features that are innovative, secure and intuitive for our users. As an important member of the engineering team, you will build solutions that affect millions of users and live streamers.', 
'- Develop TikTok LIVE gifts include 3D model rendering, animation implementation and interactive implementation.
- Optimise 3D gift performance and research the best practices of 3D rendering on mobile devices.
- Design and develop gift production tools and workflow to reduce the cost of gift production.
- Contribute innovative ideas towards gift creativity and explore graphic interactive technology that can be implemented in business.',
'Minimum Qualifications:
- Bachelor''s degree in Computer Science, or related technical field.
- Experience and knowledge of computer graphics.
- Problem-solving and communication skills.
- Experience with JavaScript, TypeScript, with solid coding ability and good abstract ability.
- Passionate about Web 3D graphics rendering and animations.
Preferred Qualifications:
- Strong on WebGL, GLSL, Three.js, Babylon.js, PixiJS etc.
- Experience with advanced techniques in real-time rendering, character animation, physics simulation and geometry modelling.
- Experience with modern mobile graphic pipeline.
- Experience with low-level performance profiling and optimization.
- Experience with 3D software such as Blender, C4D and game engines such as Unity, Unreal.
- Minimum 3 years relevant work experience from a large-scale internet business.');


INSERT INTO Job VALUES ('H11111114', 'HR','2023/03/19', 'full-time','We are on a mission to reshape the E-commerce landscape and here''s a unique opportunity for a seasoned Human Resources Business Partner to support our business teams do just that. You will be responsible for performance reviews, learning and development, and employee retention while also improving existing processes and procedures while collaborating with key stakeholders across the business. This role will actively participate in translating business plans into talent, engagement, and organization plans. Our HRBPs uniquely partner with our Talent Acquisition team to support the growth of the organization ranging from headcount planning and conducting interviews.',
'1. Partner with your business unit and ensure a deep understanding of business strategy and implement high-quality HR practices within the team.
2. Coach and mentor business leaders to help build a strong community that will improve the development of the business.
3. Collaborate with stakeholders and leadership and provide HR guidance when appropriate; including staffing, talent development, performance management, and employee relations.
4. Be the ambassador for the TikTok organizational culture as well as plan and implement activities to continue to drive employee engagement.
5. Manage HR operation activities when in needs.
6. Manage employee disciplinary issues and provide advice to business leaders on ways to manage each case.
7. Assist with recruitment efforts when necessary to ensure continued growth and success of the business.',
'1. Minimum 5 years of Human Resources working experience.
2. Strong written and oral English.
3. Comprehensive HR knowledge, especially hands-on experience in employee relations and performance management.
4. Must have extensive and in-depth knowledge of local compliance and labor laws.
5. Highly organized and self-sufficient.
6. BA/BS degree preferred.');


INSERT INTO Job VALUES ('M11111115', 'Marketing','2023/03/20', 'full-time','TikTok''s Global Business Team aims to help businesses and brands unleash their creative side, connect with our audience, and drive revenue and growth. We provide strategic input and run high-impact campaigns to ensuring our customers have best-in-class tools and products at their fingertips. B2B Marketing Manager is not afraid to think big and is also willing to roll up their sleeves to get the work done. This individual has the ability to thrive in a fast-paced environment with competing demands. A positive, team-focused attitude toward webinars and industry partnerships.',
'1. Develop and implement B2B marketing strategy to grow TikTok''s advertising business in Korea.
2. Develop messaging, narratives and collaterals to engage advertisers in Korea, including large brands, mid-market businesses and media agencies.
3. Work closely with regional and global marketing teams to localise strategies and campaigns for the Korea market.
4. Work closely with sales, PR, product and other cross-functional teams to drive marketing programs in Korea.
5. Develop local industry, customer and market insights to shape business strategy.
6. Activate integrated marketing campaigns including events, PR, advertising, social media and industry partnerships.',
'1. 8+ years of experience in marketing, communications, consulting or business strategy.
2. Experience in media, advertising or technology industries.
3. Excellent written and verbal communications in English and Korean.
4. Track record of working with and influencing sales & other cross-functional teams.
5. Experience developing integrated marketing strategies and executing go-to-market plans.
6. Strong understanding of TikTok''s solutions, the advertising industry and Korea market.');


INSERT INTO Job VALUES ('P11111116', 'Product Manager','2023/03/22', 'full-time','At TikTok, our people are humble, intelligent, compassionate and creative. We create to inspire - for you, for us, and for more than 1 billion users on our platform. We lead with curiosity and aim for the highest, never shying away from taking calculated risks and embracing ambiguity as it comes. Here, the opportunities are limitless for those who dare to pursue bold ideas that exist just beyond the boundary of possibility. Join us and make impact happen with a career at TikTok. As the Customer Product Team, our mission is to provide our customers with entertaining shopping experience in TikTok. We are looking for Senior Product Manager to join our team.',
'• Be responsible for product roadmap and product strategy design and providing TikTok users with great shopping experience and product solution.
• Be responsible for daily team management and cooperation with key stakeholders.
• Set up regular catch-ups with stakeholders on requirements, product status, feedback, and performance, to ensure an aligned OKR on a Quarterly basis.
• Take full ownership of product development, from initial requirement management to post-live analysis, and drive the best product efficiency and experience.
• Monitor quantitative product performance and collect qualitative feedback regularly after product launch, to continuously drive success metrics improvement.',
'• Bachelor''s degree or above.
• 5+ years work experience in customer products.
• Experience as a product manager or product developer.
• Excellent communication skills, data driven ability, and be able to flexibly adjust strategies in complex situations.
• Collaborate with cross function teams to define business strategy and product roadmap; provide localized shopping experience.
• Have a good understanding of e-commerce platforms, business and customers, and the ability to understand the new business models.');

INSERT INTO Job VALUES ('P11111117', 'Sales','2023/03/22', 'full-time','New Business Sales Specialists will be responsible for prospecting, qualifying, and pitching high-potential advertisers and marketing agencies for the TikTok Ads Platform. They will consult with key stakeholders to help them understand the value of the advertiser platform, and the path to get started. They will collaborate closely with internal teams to develop best practices for client acquisition and sales. They will build and manage a pipeline of opportunities while establishing new client relationships, and focusing on revenue potential.',
'- Consistently meet and exceed quantitative and qualitative acquisition sales targets, while delivering a best-in-class experience to clients.
- Prospect, qualify, pitch and close new business opportunities for the TikTok Ads Platform.
- Generate sales pipeline through outbound prospecting efforts via phone, email, and 3rd party tooling.
- Collaborate with cross functional teams on various lead operation initiatives.
- Consult with external stakeholders regarding starting their TikTok Ads strategy with identified marketing and business objectives.
- Onboard new clients onto the TikTok Ads Platform, and set them up internally for long-term growth.',
'- Bachelors degree or equivalent work experience.
- Passion for sales and/or business development.
- Excellent verbal and written English and strong communication skills.
- Experience in pipeline building through prospecting and outreaching to new customers via phone, vc, email, and other communication platforms.
- Must be able to handle confidential and sensitive information with honesty and integrity.
- Ability to think independently and strategically to develop sales acquisition strategies and tactics.
- Proven track record of exceeding performance targets.
- Previous experience in sales or business development.
- Proficient with sales prospecting tactics and technologies.');